        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens provider hook lookup and shared provider resolver projection: unreadable provider ids, aliases, hook aliases, labels, and auth fields are skipped without aborting healthy sibling providers\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `f9e2e51b6aebc8f2311f961a95c7fbfa9d65b0c7`, proven on `origin/main` at `dc4f3b57cf40553a1a53c0f7d29ca2307f0714fc`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-hook-runtime.ts src/plugins/providers.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-hook-runtime.ts src/plugins/providers.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts src/plugins/providers.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"matches providers by alias|matches providers by hook alias|skips unreadable provider hook refs|passes model refs for cli-backend runtime hook lookup|skips unreadable provider registry entries while preserving healthy providers\"`: 2 files passed, 5 selected tests passed, 110 skipped\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean after review-driven follow-up fixes\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD`: clean\n- scrubbed diff/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, and shared provider resolver projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, or hostile callback metadata while healthy sibling registrations continue.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, rebased onto `origin/main` at `dc4f3b57cf40553a1a53c0f7d29ca2307f0714fc`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran focused formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, and autoreview commands listed in Verification after the provider hook/resolver projection slice and final successful rebase/proof loop.\n\nEvidence after fix: provider runtime tests now cover unreadable provider hook refs while preserving healthy `mockplugin` hook lookup, and provider resolver tests now cover shared registry projection skipping unreadable `fuzzplugin` ids/auth while returning a plain healthy `mockplugin` provider record with stable `pluginId`, `label`, `auth`, aliases, and hook aliases.\n\nObserved result after fix: unreadable provider metadata no longer throws during provider hook lookup or shared resolver projection; unusable providers are skipped and later healthy synthetic providers remain returned with the expected plain-object provider shape.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted plugin/runtime fuzz surface plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
